00:12:11,352 --> 00:12:13,353
You don't have to worry about bleeding out or going

243
00:12:13,373 --> 00:12:14,194
into shock or anything.

244
00:12:14,474 --> 00:12:16,395
You can get your arm lopped off and you're like, uh-oh,

245
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:18,457
I should get away from whatever made that happen.

246
00:12:19,618 --> 00:12:21,419
And it obviously lacks the complexities

247
00:12:21,899 --> 00:12:23,981
of trying to accurately represent the whole spectrum

248
00:12:24,001 --> 00:12:24,821
of human vitality.

249
00:12:25,482 --> 00:12:26,282
And it doesn't try to.

250
00:12:26,602 --> 00:12:27,003
It's simple.

251
00:12:28,123 --> 00:12:30,265
So here we have another way of representing humans

252
00:12:30,325 --> 00:12:33,487
as meat in games, which is a step above abstraction,

253
00:12:33,507 --> 00:12:34,468
which is by simplifying.

254
00:12:36,122 --> 00:12:41,144
Simplification acknowledges that humans are more than just a hitbox, that we can be damaged

255
00:12:41,184 --> 00:12:47,246
in many ways and that we have more at stake than restarting a checkpoint or loading your

256
00:12:47,286 --> 00:12:47,886
last save.

257
00:12:48,867 --> 00:12:50,367
The cost now is change.

258
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:54,489
Fighting and failing, but surviving and emerging different.

259
00:12:55,249 --> 00:12:58,950
Playing Ivan, maybe I still wasn't controlling anything quite resembling a human totally,

260
00:12:59,350 --> 00:13:02,792
but it was far less abstract and it acknowledged what humanity was.

261
00:13:03,692 --> 00:13:04,192
And I liked it.

262
00:13:05,522 --> 00:13:07,964
so i did what i tend to do when i see something that i like

263
00:13:08,565 --> 00:13:10,187
i stole it and stuffed it into my game

264
00:13:11,428 --> 00:13:15,633
so this is a character in catacomb kids when you pause the menu you get this

265
00:13:15,653 --> 00:13:17,214
little view of your stats and your

266
00:13:18,035 --> 00:13:18,856
portrait of your character

267
00:13:19,977 --> 00:13:20,318
and uh...

268
00:13:20,979 --> 00:13:22,060
this is what they look like when they're

269
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,021
missing a leg

270
00:13:24,513 --> 00:13:27,154
So I added a limb system to Catacomb Kids where you can get

271
00:13:27,174 --> 00:13:30,155
your arms and legs chopped off by certain traps and enemies.

272
00:13:30,355 --> 00:13:32,956
And it's nothing as in-depth as Ivan's where it's like, oh,

273
00:13:33,076 --> 00:13:36,157
you don't have to worry about the HP of your arm or your

274
00:13:36,197 --> 00:13:39,118
torso getting critical hitted and just destroying everything.

275
00:13:40,338 --> 00:13:42,639
But if you're fighting a guy with a giant axe, you might

276
00:13:42,679 --> 00:13:45,560
want to make sure you don't come out of the fight with

277
00:13:45,620 --> 00:13:46,320
two fewer legs.

278
00:13:47,355 --> 00:13:50,216
And there's also a boss in the game called the Reaper, which

279
00:13:50,637 --> 00:13:53,739
is like, you know, death with a giant scythe. And it used to

280
00:13:53,779 --> 00:13:56,901
have a really annoying habit of chopping off all your arms and

281
00:13:56,941 --> 00:14:01,743
legs and then killing you by hitting you with them. But that

282
00:14:01,763 --> 00:14:04,445
was kind of unfair, so now he just chops off your arms and

283
00:14:04,605 --> 00:14:08,548
turns them into lightning. Again, I'm not really making a

284
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:09,768
masterpiece of realism.

285
00:14:11,358 --> 00:14:13,640
But after adding the ability to lose limbs,

286
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:15,721
something happened where there was a new fear in the game,

287
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:16,802
a new consequence,

288
00:14:16,862 --> 00:14:18,743
and like a new complication to be thrown at the player.

289
00:14:19,484 --> 00:14:23,006
Where before your only goal in each fight was to not die,

290
00:14:23,306 --> 00:14:26,728
now there's a whole new potential cost, even upon victory.

291
00:14:27,309 --> 00:14:29,830
And moreover, the cost is both meaningful and lasting.

292
00:14:30,591 --> 00:14:31,191
It changes you.

293
00:14:32,073 --> 00:14:36,715
Losing an arm removes your ability to equip offhand items and if you're a shield user that can really screw you up

294
00:14:37,036 --> 00:14:40,077
because now you have to change the entire way you play the game.

295
00:14:40,097 --> 00:14:42,558
You have to become more evasive now that you're not able to block attacks.

296
00:14:43,358 --> 00:14:47,500
Losing legs is even worse where you're forced to hop everywhere on your remaining leg

297
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:50,841
or if you lose both legs you hop on your torso stump.

298
00:14:52,082 --> 00:14:54,343
But it completely changes the feel of movement in the game

299
00:14:54,623 --> 00:14:57,744
and makes a lot of maneuvers more difficult to pull off.

300
00:14:58,264 --> 00:14:59,605
And it's super annoying.

301
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,962
probably not as bad as reversing the player's controls,

302
00:15:03,002 --> 00:15:05,866
but maybe a couple notches below that.

303
00:15:06,146 --> 00:15:08,468
By introducing these lasting consequences

304
00:15:08,488 --> 00:15:10,771
to player's actions, choices begin to have more weight.

305
00:15:11,712 --> 00:15:13,274
Decisions become more meaningful

306
00:15:13,314 --> 00:15:15,116
and the prices paid are more potent.

307
00:15:16,516 --> 00:15:19,237
So even looking at the system and realizing its simplicity,

308
00:15:20,097 --> 00:15:21,218
that it exists at all,

309
00:15:21,658 --> 00:15:23,598
adds a sense of meatiness to the player's failures.

310
00:15:23,758 --> 00:15:25,799
And really this is the core of what simplification,

311
00:15:26,919 --> 00:15:29,080
really this is the core of what simplification is

312
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:31,281
when representing human physicality in games.

313
00:15:31,761 --> 00:15:33,081
An acknowledgement that we're meat.

314
00:15:34,268 --> 00:15:37,230
We're not monolithic beings, but we break and we change.

315
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:38,791
But that's it, just an acknowledgement.

316
00:15:39,491 --> 00:15:42,113
And this is usually as far as games go when representing

317
00:15:42,153 --> 00:15:42,813
humans in games.

318
00:15:43,173 --> 00:15:44,274
I mean, how can it not be?

319
00:15:45,675 --> 00:15:49,197
We're not going to get a simulation level of breaking

320
00:15:49,237 --> 00:15:50,558
the skin, that sort of thing.

321
00:15:50,938 --> 00:15:54,320
Games will always only ever be able to present an extremely

322
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:57,381
simplified version of humans as physical creatures.

323
00:15:57,602 --> 00:15:58,382
We're too complex.

324
00:15:58,642 --> 00:15:59,723
You've got to draw the line somewhere.

325
00:16:01,896 --> 00:16:04,499
Dwarves, however, maybe we can get a little further with them.

326
00:16:05,139 --> 00:16:08,122
So Dwarf Fortress is the only real example that comes to mind of a game

327
00:16:08,162 --> 00:16:10,865
going well beyond a simplified representation of meat.

328
00:16:12,046 --> 00:16:14,728
Another game descended from the roguelike evolutionary tree,

329
00:16:15,049 --> 00:16:17,771
Dwarf Fortress does away with abstraction almost entirely

330
00:16:18,092 --> 00:16:19,573
and enters into the realm of simulation.

331
00:16:20,563 --> 00:16:23,706
Not only can your arms and legs be broken and severed as in Catacomb Kids and Ivan,

332
00:16:23,986 --> 00:16:29,992
but you can get your brain bruised, your lungs can be pierced, you can have items lodged

333
00:16:30,032 --> 00:16:34,196
in your flesh and there are pain values associated with certain types of injuries.

334
00:16:34,696 --> 00:16:38,600
If your heart is punctured, you don't die because your HP reaches zero, you die because

335
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:41,403
your blood loss becomes too great to sustain your life any further.

336
00:16:42,744 --> 00:16:45,507
If you'll indulge me, a quote from the Dwarf Fortress wiki page.

337
00:16:46,325 --> 00:16:50,426
Guts. Damage to guts causes great pain and nausea. Creatures

338
00:16:50,446 --> 00:16:52,627
will vomit and then retch repeatedly depending on how much

339
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:56,048
damage is caused. This slows the creature and can dehydrate them.

340
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:59,990
When guts are pierced, they may spill out of the wound. This

341
00:17:00,030 --> 00:17:02,591
causes a lot of bleeding and exposes the guts themselves as a

342
00:17:02,631 --> 00:17:05,652
target for aimed attacks. Slicing off the exposed guts

343
00:17:05,692 --> 00:17:10,614
causes heavy bleeding and almost always death. The cut off guts

344
00:17:10,634 --> 00:17:12,215
can then be picked up and used as a weapon.

345
00:17:15,373 --> 00:17:22,575
So simulation goes above and beyond the expected representation of human physicality in games.

346
00:17:22,935 --> 00:17:26,696
It strives to do more than just enhance a sense of meatiness, more than just present

347
00:17:26,736 --> 00:17:30,656
for fragility and resilience, but it unifies your character with the laws of the world

348
00:17:30,676 --> 00:17:31,157
they inhabit.

349
00:17:31,577 --> 00:17:34,517
The line is blurred between what's a part of them and what's a part of the world.

350
00:17:34,597 --> 00:17:37,338
Where does the self stop and the laws of the wider universe take over?

351
00:17:38,158 --> 00:17:38,798
There is no line.

352
00:17:38,938 --> 00:17:39,579
They're the same.

353
00:17:39,959 --> 00:17:43,540
They're not only in the world, but held together by it and torn apart by it, and then they

354
00:17:43,580 --> 00:17:43,940
become it.

355
00:17:44,915 --> 00:17:46,356
So this is what simulation means to me.

356
00:17:46,896 --> 00:17:49,038
Employing the nuances of our physical existence

357
00:17:49,338 --> 00:17:51,480
to blur the line between the player characters

358
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:52,421
and the worlds they inhabit.

359
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:55,684
They're both existing within the world

360
00:17:55,784 --> 00:17:58,026
and are a world unto themselves.

361
00:18:00,122 --> 00:18:02,343
So abstraction, simplification, and simulation.

362
00:18:02,463 --> 00:18:05,585
Each of these categories can and does mix and mingle

363
00:18:05,605 --> 00:18:08,266
with the others to greater and lesser degrees.

364
00:18:08,886 --> 00:18:11,027
Games with largely abstract health systems

365
00:18:11,088 --> 00:18:12,988
supplemented by a suggestion of hit location

366
00:18:13,028 --> 00:18:14,769
like a lot of first person shooters have

367
00:18:14,789 --> 00:18:18,111
with headshots and other sort of tertiary damage.

368
00:18:19,011 --> 00:18:21,012
Or games where the player is represented

369
00:18:21,052 --> 00:18:23,534
as a breakable being, a mutable collection of parts

370
00:18:23,914 --> 00:18:26,195
working alongside a more familiar abstract system

371
00:18:26,235 --> 00:18:27,055
like with Catacomb Kids.

372
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:30,174
And games like The Long Dark and other recent survival sims

373
00:18:30,194 --> 00:18:32,615
that skew towards the simulation side of simplicity.

374
00:18:32,955 --> 00:18:35,156
Or Cataclysm, Dark Days Ahead, which is another roguelike,

375
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:36,936
which straddles the line between simplicity

376
00:18:36,956 --> 00:18:37,916
and simulation altogether,

377
00:18:38,157 --> 00:18:39,957
while still having some abstracted aspects.

378
00:18:40,237 --> 00:18:41,918
Nothing is ever as cut and dry as just,

379
00:18:42,098 --> 00:18:44,678
oh, that's simulation, or oh, that's simplistic,

380
00:18:44,719 --> 00:18:45,759
or oh, that's abstract.

381
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:51,721
And so, like, this is some of, I tried to map some,

382
00:18:51,741 --> 00:18:52,721
I don't know if they're accurate.

383
00:18:54,441 --> 00:18:54,581
But.

384
00:18:55,606 --> 00:18:58,829
So far, while I've mostly been talking about how damage is sustained in games,

385
00:18:58,869 --> 00:19:00,932
there's a whole other side to this equation.

386
00:19:01,953 --> 00:19:02,573
The aftermath.

387
00:19:03,174 --> 00:19:04,375
How we heal, how we adapt.

388
00:19:04,515 --> 00:19:07,378
Once the damage is done and the danger is passed, what then?

389
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:10,512
Well, there's an old saying that time heals all wounds,

390
00:19:10,532 --> 00:19:12,834
but rarely is the sentiment ever present in games.

391
00:19:13,274 --> 00:19:14,635
You're always looking for a med kit,

392
00:19:14,915 --> 00:19:16,036
or popping a healing potion,

393
00:19:16,056 --> 00:19:17,517
or like calling a cleric to heal you.

394
00:19:17,537 --> 00:19:19,879
And Catacomb Kids is guilty of this as well.

395
00:19:20,359 --> 00:19:21,960
Restoring your severed limbs is as simple

396
00:19:22,021 --> 00:19:24,082
as just drinking a potion of regeneration

397
00:19:24,102 --> 00:19:26,104
or casting the regenerate spell on yourself,

398
00:19:26,404 --> 00:19:27,144
if you know it.

399
00:19:28,605 --> 00:19:30,167
And your limbs come back a bit weaker

400
00:19:30,587 --> 00:19:32,388
than your original limbs and blue,

401
00:19:33,229 --> 00:19:34,890
but they serve the, you know,

402
00:19:34,930 --> 00:19:36,331
the new limbs serve the purpose well enough.

403
00:19:37,221 --> 00:19:39,262
If you become diseased or poisoned, a health potion will

404
00:19:39,282 --> 00:19:40,122
make you right in an instant.

405
00:19:40,522 --> 00:19:41,623
It's all very active healing.

406
00:19:42,083 --> 00:19:43,423
So this is what active healing is.

407
00:19:43,964 --> 00:19:45,424
Do thing, get better.

408
00:19:47,505 --> 00:19:48,445
But rarely is there waiting.

409
00:19:49,206 --> 00:19:52,367
I mean, maybe there's a little animation for drinking a

410
00:19:52,407 --> 00:19:55,708
potion, or you might have to sit still for a second while

411
00:19:55,748 --> 00:19:56,728
your shields recharge.

412
00:19:59,609 --> 00:20:02,050
But beyond that, recovery is usually a matter of fairly low

413
00:20:02,130 --> 00:20:02,711
consequence.

414
00:20:03,071 --> 00:20:04,371
It's always a good thing.

415
00:20:04,731 --> 00:20:05,552
You want to recover.

416
00:20:05,592 --> 00:20:06,272
You want to heal.

417
00:20:07,245 --> 00:20:10,749
In many roguelikes, you can sit still and spend a few turns

418
00:20:11,309 --> 00:20:13,111
sort of waiting for your health to replenish.

419
00:20:13,171 --> 00:20:16,615
But the games are usually already so abstract that this

420
00:20:16,735 --> 00:20:18,337
doesn't really do a lot in the way of

421
00:20:18,397 --> 00:20:19,738
representing a human need.

422
00:20:19,798 --> 00:20:21,761
It's just more of like a mechanical thing where, oh, if

423
00:20:21,801 --> 00:20:23,142
you stand still, your health will go up.

424
00:20:24,143 --> 00:20:25,485
It's just like barely on the cusp of

425
00:20:25,545 --> 00:20:26,546
simplicity and abstraction.

426
00:20:28,062 --> 00:20:31,605
but there's no like cleaning your wounds and bandaging them, there's no uh... like

427
00:20:31,665 --> 00:20:34,768
keeping the bed as you wait for the poison in you to run its course

428
00:20:35,508 --> 00:20:37,130
there's no actually going to a hospital

429
00:20:38,310 --> 00:20:42,094
not a haunted hospital full of like demons and stuff, just a normal

430
00:20:42,214 --> 00:20:43,234
functioning hospital

431
00:20:43,254 --> 00:20:47,918
I don't know, those seem kind of rare to me in games for some reason

432
00:20:49,294 --> 00:20:53,137
Somehow games always seem to have medicine that makes time irrelevant.

433
00:20:53,737 --> 00:20:57,140
And I get it. Don't think I'm suggesting that in shoot-em-ups

434
00:20:57,420 --> 00:21:01,443
and shooters you should have a long hospital stay

435
00:21:01,823 --> 00:21:05,386
after every gunfight where you're just sitting around playing crossword puzzles

436
00:21:05,706 --> 00:21:06,306
and coding.

437
00:21:07,427 --> 00:21:08,728
I mean, maybe that would be interesting.

438
00:21:10,289 --> 00:21:13,371
But for the time cost of injury

439
00:21:13,651 --> 00:21:17,514
to be so ubiquitously absent in games is a curious thing.

440
00:21:18,407 --> 00:21:20,567
And it's not like there haven't been time-sensitive games before.

441
00:21:20,587 --> 00:21:23,428
There's like Shenmue, Majora's Mask, and Harvest Moon games.

442
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:25,348
These all, like, run on a clock.

443
00:21:26,448 --> 00:21:29,289
So, like, maybe in Harvest Moon you could, like, get kicked in the head by your horse

444
00:21:29,689 --> 00:21:30,749
and then, like, get knocked out.

445
00:21:31,109 --> 00:21:34,590
And then you, like, spend a week in the hospital waiting to recover

446
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:36,990
and during that time your crops aren't getting taken care of

447
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:39,891
and your horse is, like, really sad

448
00:21:39,911 --> 00:21:41,871
because he's like, I'm sorry, guy. I didn't mean to kick you.

449
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:48,098
But it would cost the most valuable time,

450
00:21:48,118 --> 00:21:50,220
the most valuable resource that you have in the game,

451
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:53,641
or that we have as existing beings, which is time.

452
00:21:54,902 --> 00:21:56,923
Your crops won't wait, like Majora's Mask,

453
00:21:57,103 --> 00:21:58,044
the falling moon wouldn't wait

454
00:21:58,084 --> 00:21:59,905
if you lost time as a failure.

455
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:02,626
And in Shenmue, you'd lose time

456
00:22:02,666 --> 00:22:06,188
and then you'd be closer to not getting revenge.

457
00:22:07,249 --> 00:22:09,170
And a lot of things can happen

458
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:11,451
in the absence of a person's unwellness.

459
00:22:12,671 --> 00:22:13,632
And then there's coping.

460
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:17,865
Accepting that whatever injuries you've sustained, whatever scars you've received,

461
00:22:18,125 --> 00:22:22,167
they're just a part of you now. You adapt and recalibrate and learn to move forward

462
00:22:22,207 --> 00:22:27,490
through your new normal. Old familiar obstacles become new challenges. Maybe you learn to overcome

463
00:22:27,530 --> 00:22:33,193
them again, or with some ingenuity or a different approach, or maybe you don't and find a different

464
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,493
new path to take.

465
00:22:37,493 --> 00:22:40,596
But humans, I think, are incredible.

466
00:22:41,197 --> 00:22:43,178
And maybe I'm the only one, but I'm constantly amazed

467
00:22:43,198 --> 00:22:45,801
by the fact that we live for as long as we do,

468
00:22:45,861 --> 00:22:47,682
despite all the million little random things

469
00:22:47,722 --> 00:22:49,644
that could go wrong every second.

470
00:22:50,565 --> 00:22:53,687
And we're still tenacious enough to keep existing as meat.

471
00:22:55,609 --> 00:22:57,911
I look at us and I feel like the aliens feel

472
00:22:57,971 --> 00:22:59,592
from Terry Bisson's story.

473
00:22:59,993 --> 00:23:01,234
Like, we're made out of meat?

474
00:23:01,354 --> 00:23:01,794
Like, really?

475
00:23:01,814 --> 00:23:04,096
And look what the things that we can do.

476
00:23:06,035 --> 00:23:09,638
And games. Games are, as I have mentioned, pretty cool. I like them.

477
00:23:10,659 --> 00:23:17,264
And I feel like they're able to give us a unique perspective and let us act as through the mind and body of another.

478
00:23:17,985 --> 00:23:24,390
And in doing so, perhaps, let us come to a better understanding of some meat that isn't us, some person that isn't us.

479
00:23:24,851 --> 00:23:31,476
And so I've been speaking until now of people as meat, our parts as physical qualities on the most general scale.

480
00:23:32,428 --> 00:23:35,970
because that does interest me and I do find it fascinating. I want to play more games where I'm

481
00:23:36,330 --> 00:23:40,952
fearful and breakable and forced to live with the consequences of my failures and shortcomings

482
00:23:41,312 --> 00:23:45,294
but still somehow continue and grow beyond them. I want to play a game where I'm parts and I am

483
00:23:45,354 --> 00:23:51,697
fragile and I am resilient. But obviously people are more than me. People are hopes and loves

484
00:23:52,098 --> 00:23:54,179
and hates, hurts, friends, memories.

485
00:23:55,243 --> 00:23:56,524
Not every story starts with all 100...

486
00:23:56,784 --> 00:23:57,965
or not all...

487
00:23:58,245 --> 00:24:01,848
